oney and Clover#Live-action film|Honey and Clover]]''\n| Y\u016bta Takemoto\n| Lead role\n|-\n| ''Kisarazu Cat's Eye: World Series''\n| Futoshi Nakagomi (Bambi)\n| \n|-\n| 2007\n| ''Kiiroi Namida''\n| Ry\u016bsan Mukai\n| Lead role with Arashi members\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Yatterman (film)|Yatterman]]''\n| Gan-chan\n| Lead role\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Kamisama no Karute]]''\n| Ichito Kurihara\n| Lead role with [[Aoi Miyazaki]]\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Nazotoki wa Dinner no Ato de]]'' (movie)\n| Kageyama\n| Lead role with [[Keiko Kitagawa]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2014\n| ''[[Kamisama no Karute 2]]''\n| Ichito Kurihara\n| Lead role with [[Aoi Miyazaki]]\n|-\n| ''Pikanchi Life is Hard Tabun Happy''\n| Tadashi Kamogawa (Chu)\n| Lead role with Arashi members\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Laplace's Witch (film)|Laplace's Witch]]''\n| Sh\u016bsuke Aoe\n| Lead role\n|-\n|}\n\n== Stage ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1997\n|''Kyo to Kyo''\n|\n|\n|-\n|1998\n|''Kyo to Kyo''\n| Tokyo Hamamatsuch\u014d\n|\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''West Side Story''\n| Tony\n|rowspan=\"2\"| Lead role\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''The Beautiful Game'' \n| John Kelly\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Organization\n! Award\n! Work\n! Result\n|-\n| 2002||5th Nikkan Sports Drama Grand Prix||Best Newcomer||''Tengoku ni Ichiban Chikai Otoko 2''||{{won}}<ref name=\"tengoku_award\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2009||61st Television Drama Academy Awards||Best Actor||''The Quiz Show 2''||{{nom}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.television.co.jp/drama/academy/2009/07/post_338.html|script-title=ja:\u4e3b\u6f14\u7537\u512a\u8cde|date=July 22, 2009|language=Japanese|publisher=Television Drama Academy Awards|accessdate=November 21, 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[GQ]] Japan Men of the Year 2009 Awards||GQ Man of the Year 2009{{#tag:ref|Sakurai was one of the five honorees for GQ Men of the Year 2009.<ref name=\"GQ2\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gqjapan.jp/event/menoftheyear2009/|title=GQ Men of the Year 2009|language=Japanese|work=[[GQ]]|accessdate=December 16, 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20091026171236/http://www.gqjapan.jp/event/menoftheyear2009/|archivedate=October 26, 2009}}</ref>|group=fn}}||||{{won}}<ref name=\"GQ\" /><ref name=\"GQ2\" />\n|-\n| 2010||64th Television Drama Academy Awards||Best Actor||''Tokujo Kabachi!!''||{{nom}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.television.co.jp/drama/academy/2010/04/post_360.html|script-title=ja:\u4e3b\u6f14\u7537\u512a\u8cde|date=April 21, 2010|language=Japanese|publisher=Television Drama Academy Awards|accessdate=June 20, 2010}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2012||21st Annual TV Life Awards||Best Actor||rowspan=\"2\"|''Nazotoki wa Dinner no Ato De''||{{won}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvlife.jp/special/drama-gp/2011k.php|script-title=ja:\u300c\u7b2c21\u56de\u5e74\u9593\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u5927\u8cde2011\u300d\u4e3b\u6f14\u7537\u512a\u8cde\uff01|date=February 15, 2012|language=Japanese|publisher=Tvlife.jp|accessdate=February 15, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120502011811/http://www.tvlife.jp/special/drama-gp/2011k.php|archivedate=May 2, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| 71st Television Drama Academy Awards||Best Actor||{{nom}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.television.co.jp/drama/academy/2012/02/post_781.html|script-title=ja:\u4e3b\u6f14\u7537\u512a\u8cde|date=February 17, 2012|language=Japanese|publisher=Television Drama Academy Awards|accessdate=February 17, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2013||17th Nikkan Sports Drama Grand Prix (Spring)||Best Actor||rowspan=\"3\"|''Kazoku Game''||{{won}}\n|-\n| 77th Television Drama Academy Awards||Best Actor||{{won}}\n|-\n| 2014||23rd Annual TV Life Awards||Best Actor||{{won}}<ref>{{cite web|title=2013\u5e74\u300c\u5e74\u9593\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u5927\u8cde\u300d\u306f\u6afb\u4e95\u7fd4\u4e3b\u6f14\u300e\u5bb6\u65cf\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u300f\u306b\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01|url=http://www.tvlife.jp/2014/02/26/18065|publish